
<input>
Type attribute changes what the input will be

<input type=“" placeholder="">

Placeholder is the text that appears before you type

Labels

Labels are linked to whatever input is in the script

For instance 

<div class=“preference”>
	<label form="cheese”>Do you like cheese?</label>
	<input type="checkox” name="cheese” id=cheese”>
</div>

<!--Keeping this here for now-->

<label for="username">Enter a username:</label>
<input id="username" type=""text" placeholder=""username">

<label for="password">Enter a password</label>
<input type="password" placeholder="password" id="password">

</label>